[SN]TITLE[SN]
Rio Olympics 2016: Giles Scott wins GB's fifth successive Finn title

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Giles Scott sealed gold in sailing's Finn class to give Great Britain their fifth successive Olympic title in the event.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The Weymouth-based 29-year-old succeeds Sir Ben Ainslie, who won the previous three titles, and will now join the ex-Olympian's 2017 America's Cup team.
"It's an amazing achievement for Giles. He really has been totally dominant," Ainslie told BBC South Today.
Scott's victory gave Great Britain their 17th gold medal of the Games.
