The champion took an unassailable lead going into Tuesday's medal race, winning three of the 11 races in the competition.
Ainslie added: "To win gold without having to even compete in the medal races is rare."
Scott came second in the final race and finished with a total score of 36 points. Slovenia's Vasilij Zbogar took silver with 68 points and USA's Caleb Paine, who won the final race, finished third with 76 points.
