Scott said on Monday: "It's been a long road. I campaigned properly for London, missed out on the qualification for that and was bitterly disappointed.
"Watching all of my friends racing at the Olympics and get medals wasn't easy, but the amazing thing that came off the back of it was a desire to right the wrongs I felt I made, and to put together a campaign I could be proud of and just really work my ass off for three years."
